SS dug out of the hole, sending up another smoke-screen to avoid 
Perceptors fire, and managed to transform and jog at a fair pace to 
Tyreal

--- In nbwrpg@y..., "warriorazure" <wingedwarrior41@h...> wrote:
> The techno-organic fabric of the two Tripredacus had seemingly 
drove 
> them in a foggy unconscious state. As a result, they were hit by 
all 
> the shots that came at them. This broke their reverie.
> 
> Tyrael stood up and looked around. He took flight and tried to 
grasp 
> the situation. The predacon goons seemed to be falling back, but he 
> could only see Burrock and Shadow Star, whereas Talon was nowhere 
to 
> be seen.
> 
> Tyrael: TRIPREDACUS! REGROUP! WE WILL PUSH THEM BACK FURTHER IF WE 
> CONCENTRATE FIRE!
> 
> Burrock went to where Shadow Star was and smiled. He didn't know 
who 
> he was shooting at, but he shot acidic spikes.
> 
> Burrock: Hehe... I like this new order...
